{{Location map|Japan Shimane Prefecture| label = Tsukuriyama Kofun Group| position = top| mark = Red pog.svg| marksize = 10| relief = 1| width = 250| caption={{left|Location.}}}}

'''Tsukuriyama Kofun Group''' (造山古墳群) is an {{ill|Kofun group|ja|古墳群|1=Kofun cluster|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun group|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun cluster|qq=}} from the [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]] located in [[:en:Yasugi, Shimane|Yasugi, Shimane]], [[:en:Shimane Prefecture|Shimane Prefecture]]. Together with other nearby Kofun groups, it has been collectively designated as the "'''Arashima Kofun Group''' (荒島古墳群)" and recognized as a [[:en:Historic site|Historic site of Japan]]} by the Japanese government.<ref name=shimanebunkazai>{{Cite web|author=Shimane Prefecture Education and Cultural Properties Division|url=https://www.pref.shimane.lg.jp/life/bunka/bunkazai/shiseki/kunisiseki.html|title=List of National Cultural Properties [Historic Sites]|work=Shimane Prefecture|accessdate=2023-08-27}}</ref><ref name=bunkaisan>{{Cite web|author=Agency for Cultural Affairs|url=https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/172875|title=Arashima Kofun Group|work=Cultural Heritage Online|accessdate=2023-08-27}}</ref>{{Refnest|group=Note|Tsukuriyama is categorized as a '''subgroup of the Arashima Kofun Group'''.<ref name=bunkaisan/>}} It is also part of the broader {{ill|Arashima Kofun Cluster|ja|荒島墳墓群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arashima Kofuns|qq=}}. The Yasugi City government has developed the area into a historical park named "'''Ancient Izumo Royal Mausoleum Hill'''".<ref name=shimaneOuryounooka>{{Cite web|author=Shimane Prefecture Education and Cultural Properties Division|url=https://www.pref.shimane.lg.jp/life/bunka/bunkazai/shiseki/shisekidesu/shiseki01.html|title=Shimane Historic Sites: Ancient Izumo Royal Mausoleum Hill|work=Shimane Prefecture|accessdate=2023-08-27}}</ref><ref name=yasukiOuryounooka>{{Cite web|author=Yasugi City Tourism Association|url=https://yasugi-kankou.com/spot/spot-482/|title=Ancient Izumo Royal Mausoleum Hill|work=Yasugi City Tourism Guide|accessdate=2023-08-27}}</ref>.

== Overview ==

[[File:造山1号墳出土 円筒埴輪 (J-34492).JPG|thumb|160px|right|{{center|Cylindrical haniwa from Tsukuriyama 1 Kofun}}{{small|Exhibited at [[:en:Tokyo National Museum|Tokyo National Museum]].}}]]
'''Tsukuriyama 1 Kofun''' is a {{ill|square-shaped Kofun|ja|方墳|1=Square Kofun|1=Square Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/square-shaped Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Square Kofun|qq=}} measuring 60 meters on each side, one of the largest square mounds from the early Kofun period nationwide. Excavations in [[:en:Shōwa era|1936]] (Shōwa 11) and 1938 (Shōwa 13) revealed a {{ill|pit-style stone chamber|ja|竪穴式石室|1=Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=竪穴式石室|4=zh|5=豎穴式石室|1=Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/pit-style stone chamber|13=User:Immanuelle/Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|qq=}}. Buried artifacts include {{ill|triangular-rimmed deity-and-beast mirrors|ja|三角縁神獣鏡|1=Triangular-Rimmed Divine Beast Mirror|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/triangular-rimmed deity-and-beast mirrors|13=User:Immanuelle/Triangular-Rimmed Divine Beast Mirror|qq=}}, [[:en:TLV mirror|square-rim deity-and-animal mirrors]], spindle-shaped stone artifacts, glass {{ill|Kudatama|lt=Kudatama|lt=Tubular beads|ja|管玉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/tubular beads|qq=}}, iron swords, and {{ill|Kozuka|lt=Kozuka|lt=Ko-dachi|ja|刀子|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ko-dachi|qq=}}. On December 16, 1936, it was designated a National Historic Site under the name "Tsukuriyama Kofun."{{Sfn|Nagami|Miyake|1992|p=1}}

'''Tsukuriyama 3 Kofun''' is a square mound dating to the early Kofun period, measuring 38 meters in length and 30 meters in width. Excavations in {{ill|1965|ja|昭和40|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1965|qq=}} uncovered a pit-style stone chamber yielding a {{ill|two-deity two-beast mirror|ja|斜縁神獣鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/two-deity two-beast mirror|qq=}}, jasper tubular beads, glass beads, a ko-dachi, and a yari-ganna. It was designated a Shimane Prefecture Historic Site on May 31, 1965.{{Sfn|Nagami|Miyake|1992|p=1}}

On the highest point of the hill, there is '''Tsukuriyama 2 Kofun''', a {{ill|keyhole-shaped mound|ja|前方後方墳|lt=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|1=Zenpō-kōhō-fun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/keyhole-shaped mound|13=User:Immanuelle/zenpō-kōhō-fun|qq=}} measuring 50 meters in length, and the smaller '''Tsukuriyama 4 Kofun'''. Both were excavated in 1991, revealing construction dating to the early 6th century.{{Sfn|Nagami|Miyake|1992}} A fifth mound, '''Tsukuriyama 5 Kofun''', is located slightly apart from the main group.

Nearby, the '''Ōnari Kofun''', another square mound from the early Kofun period, is the largest of its kind nationally. Excavations in {{ill|1911|ja|明治44|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1911|qq=}} revealed artifacts such as triangular-rimmed deity-and-beast mirrors and a {{ill|sokantō|ja|素環頭大刀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/sokantō|qq=}}. A reproduction of the sokantō, crafted by master swordsmith {{ill|Kawachi Kunihira|ja|河内国平|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawachi Kunihira|qq=}}, is exhibited at the {{ill|Yasugi City Wako Museum|ja|和鋼博物館|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yasugi City Wako Museum|qq=}}.

== Cultural Properties ==
Initially, Tsukuriyama 1 Kofun was designated as a National Historic Site, and Tsukuriyama 3 Kofun was designated as a Shimane Prefecture Historic Site. In 1999, the Agency for Cultural Affairs expanded the designation to include Tsukuriyama Kofun Group (2-4 Kofun), Ōnari Kofun, and the Shiozuyama Burial Group (1-11 Kofun), officially renaming them the "'''Arashima Kofun Group'''".<ref name=shimanebunkazai/><ref name=bunkaisan/>

